After a tremendous amount of research and testing by Bill Wilson and the Wilson Combat team we are excited to announce the availability of our custom AR platform rifles chambered in 6.8 SPC caliber.

postcontent:
Remington 700 in 308 with the following 
-glass bedded and trued action, done by a gunsmith 
-24 inch Sendero profile barrel also installed by a gunsmith (almost M24 thickness) 
-Bell and Carlson stock 
-CDI bottom metal

CDI bottom, made to take AICS magazines. Below is a link and review to the item. Keep in mind these are +/-200, plus a 10 rd AICS magazine is 80-90, and then you have to pay a gunsmith to put it in. 
http://www.snipercentral.com/cdidbm.phtml 

Magazine 
http://www.midwayusa.com/product/478419/accuracy-international-magazine-accuracy-international-chassis-system-aics-short-action-308-winchester-10-round-steel-matte?cm_vc=subv1468203 

Stock is a Bell and Carlson, link below is to MidwayUSA. 
http://www.midwayusa.com/product/486263/bell-and-carlson-medalist-light-tactical-rifle-stock-remington-700-bdl-short-action-with-aluminum-bedding-block-system-varmint-barrel-channel-synthetic-black 

Barrel is a non fluted Sendero barrel, which along with a 5R is widely known as the most accurate production barrel from Remington. The Charleston county SWAT team bought Senderos, and immediately changed out barrels and the gunsmith had a few sitting around and sold it to me and installed it, and he also glass bedded and trued the action for me. The barrel is of course free floating. 

So I can break down components. 
Original rifle - 400 at academy 
Stock - 300 at midway 
Bottom metal - 200 
Magazine - 90 
Barrel - 300 
Harris Bipod - 90 
Scope and hardware - 400 

Total for components-1780. That is no shipping and no labor.. Add another few hundred for labor. So as you can see you are getting a pretty good deal. I don't think you could build a gun this good for the price I'm asking, unless you're a gunsmith, and even then it would be tough. And this one was put together right, and it shoots. You won't need to tinker with it to make it work, I'll give you my ammo recipe and KAC ballistics data. 

If you want to get into the long range precision game this is a good starting point. The things that most shooters do to their rifles for accuracy and consistency are already done on this rifle, it's ready to go and zeroed for 200 yds. The only original part is the action. 

This gun is a .5 MOA gun with FGMM or handloads. I have shot steel at 800 yds with it. If you are local to the Charleston SC area and are interested you are welcome to shoot it first. Note the pic is of a group at 600 yds. The 4th shot is not a flier, I adjusted to hit center mass with a call from my spotter.

I prefer to do a face to face, I am willing to drive or ship if i need to. Pics are two posts down. Asking 1500 shipped, 1300 if you don't want the scope. I am selling to fund a SCAR17.

title: For Sale:  Colt Official Police .38 spl
postcontent:
The Colt Official Police was first introduced to the market in 1927. A medium frame, six shot, double action revolver, chambered in .38 special. The target market for this pistol was primarily law enforcement and it became one of the best selling police firearms of all time. The Colt Official Police was also used by various U.S. and allied military forces during WW II.

This revolver, according to Colt's Proof House was manufactured in 1943, is in very good condition. It is obvious when you look at this firearm, it was very important to the original owner and it has been well cared for over the years. Both the trigger and hammer have been jeweled and worked, resulting in an remarkably crisp trigger pull. Functionally the timing appears to be on and the cylinder locks up tight. At some point in time someone attached a grip adapter to this weapon and a small hole remains in the frame; however, rather than attaching another adapter I felt leaving the revolver in its original condition was the best thing to do. This firearm is in very good condition, while it has some minor wear on the high points as well as the barrel and the grips have been rubbed on the right side, I believe this is a gem. The photo's which are attached to this auction show an honest and fair representation of the condition of this revolver. This is a wonderful opportunity to own a very collectable Colt which is rich in its history and service to this country. If you have any questions, please contact me
